  id: External_abdominal_oblique_muscle.R
  partName: External abdominal oblique muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - 'The right external abdominal oblique muscle forms part of the superficial abdominal
    wall and extends along the lateral side of the canine trunk. It originates from
    the caudal ribs and thoracolumbar fascia before attaching to the abdominal midline
    and pelvis. This muscle assists in trunk flexion, bending , and rotational movements '
  - and rotational movements while stabilizing the body during walking, running,
    and jumping. It also compresses the abdominal cavity, supporting internal organs
    and aiding forceful expiration during respiration. Working together with other
    abdominal muscles, it contributes significantly to posture and core strength.
